olute mt-20 opacity-0" id=3D"objective" data-id=3D"hab_objective"></a><br><=
p class=3D"font-normal ">Saved Supergroups can be re-used across Rippling. =
They can be created in the Saved Supergroups app or on the fly when definin=
g a group elsewhere in Rippling.</p><br><p class=3D"font-normal ">For an ov=
erview of Supergroups and how they can help you make the most of Rippling, =
review our <a class=3D"font-normal text-blue-600 hover:cursor-pointer" href=
=3D"https://help.rippling.com/article?articleId=3D945615220635">introductio=
n to Supergroups</a>.</p><br><a class=3D"absolute opacity-0 scroll-mt-40" i=
d=3D"permissions-required" data-id=3D"hat_permissions-required"></a><h2 cla=
ss=3D"text-4xl font-bold" id=3D"permissions-required" data-id=3D"permission=
s-required">Permissions required</h2><a class=3D"absolute mt-20 opacity-0" =
id=3D"permissions-required" data-id=3D"hab_permissions-required"></a><br><p=
 class=3D"font-normal ">To create a saved Supergroup, you must have certain=
 permissions. Learn more in <a class=3D"font-normal text-blue-600 hover:cur=
sor-pointer" href=3D"https://help.rippling.com/article?articleId=3D28894930=
6589">our overview of access for Supergroups</a>.</p><br><a class=3D"absolu=
te opacity-0 scroll-mt-40" id=3D"create-a-saved-supergroup-in-the-saved-sup=
ergroups-app" data-id=3D"hat_create-a-saved-supergroup-in-the-saved-supergr=
oups-app"></a><h2 class=3D"text-4xl font-bold" id=3D"create-a-saved-supergr=
oup-in-the-saved-supergroups-app" data-id=3D"create-a-saved-supergroup-in-t=
he-saved-supergroups-app">Create a saved Supergroup in the Saved Supergroup=
s app</h2><a class=3D"absolute mt-20 opacity-0" id=3D"create-a-saved-superg=
roup-in-the-saved-supergroups-app" data-id=3D"hab_create-a-saved-supergroup=
-in-the-saved-supergroups-app"></a><br><p class=3D"font-normal ">To create =
a saved Supergroup in the Saved Supergroups app, follow these steps:</p><br=
><ol class=3D" list-[decimal]  pl-8"><li class=3D"items-start"><p class=3D"=
font-normal ">From the sidebar, select <b>Company</b> <b>Settings</b> &gt; =
<b>Saved Supergroups</b>.</p></li><li class=3D"items-start"><p class=3D"fon=
t-normal ">On the <i class=3D"italic">Saved Supergroups</i> tab, click <b>C=
reate group</b>.</p></li><li class=3D"items-start"><p class=3D"font-normal =
">Give the group a <b>name</b>. The name must be unique=E2=80=94it cannot b=
e the same as any other saved Supergroup.</p></li><li class=3D"items-start"=
><p class=3D"font-normal ">Optionally, give the group a <b>description</b>.=
 This can be helpful to summarize the contents of the group.</p></li><li cl=
ass=3D"items-start"><p class=3D"font-normal ">In the <b>Include</b> box, ad=
d the attributes defining who you want to include in the group. In the <b>E=
xcept</b> box, add attributes for anyone you want to exclude from the group=
.For example, to include people in the Chicago office, add <i class=3D"ital=
ic">Work Location &gt; Chicago office</i> in the Include box. To exclude co=
ntractors, add <i class=3D"italic">Employment Types &gt; Contractor/1099 em=
